> Salsa fresca is our favorite way to channel warm-weather vibes all year round. It's
> juicy and tangy with a touch of heat, making it the perfect complement to crispy,
> turmeric-and-cumin-spiced barramundi. The fillets are served on top of steamy quinoa
> and blanketed in lime crema and said salsa. No matter the temperature, one bite of
> this delicious dish will make everything feel a whole lot sunnier.

Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed), separating whites
from greens. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Mince @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Zest and quarter
@lime{1} (for 4 servings, zest one lime and quarter both). Mince @chili pepper{1}(minced).

== Turmeric Quinoa ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the scallion
whites and @turmeric{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings); cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}
(you'll use more turmeric later).

Add @water{1%cup}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}.
Bring to a boil, then stir in @quinoa{1/2%cup}. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook
until quinoa is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Salsa Fresca ==

While quinoa cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine tomatoes, cilantro, remaining
scallion whites, and juice from half the lime. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. If you like your salsa spicy, stir in chili to taste.

== Lime Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, a big squeeze of lime juice, and
as much lime zest as you like. Stir in @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches
a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Spice Mixture ==

In a second small bowl, combine @cumin{1%tsp} and @turmeric{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4
servings). (Be sure to measure the turmeric—we sent more.)

== Barramundi ==

Pat @barramundi{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Season flesh sides with spice mixture.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add barramundi skin sides down and cook until skin is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Flip and cook until fish is opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> Barramundi is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145º.

== To Serve ==

Fluff quinoa with a #fork{}; stir in scallion greens and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4
servings) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide between #plates{}. Top quinoa with barramundi; garnish with salsa fresca and
crema. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.